2026-03-09
- Investigating standalone config save failure:
  - user-facing error: `command /start chain step 1: inline_button requires text and buttons json`
  - active saved bot JSON does not currently contain an `inline_button` step in `/start`
  - failure occurs while parsing submitted form data before config is written
- Root cause found:
  - chain-step serialization in the standalone Vue config editor is line-based and pipe-delimited
  - parsers in `config_vue.js` and `token_ui.py` split raw chain step text on newline and `|`
  - multiline message text inside a chained `inline_button` step breaks the payload into multiple lines, so the backend sees an incomplete `inline_button` definition
- Fix plan:
  - switch chain-step serialization to one JSON object per line for new saves
  - keep legacy pipe-delimited parsing for backward compatibility
  - add regression coverage for multiline chained `inline_button` content
- Implemented:
  - `src/etrax/standalone/config_vue.js`
    - chain-step save path now serializes normalized module steps as JSON lines
    - chain-step load path now tries JSON first, then falls back to legacy pipe-delimited parsing
  - `src/etrax/standalone/token_ui.py`
    - backend chain-step parser now accepts JSON-line payloads for command and callback pipelines
    - backend UI-state serializer now emits JSON-line payloads, preserving multiline text safely
  - `tests/test_token_ui.py`
    - added multiline `inline_button` chain-step regression coverage
