[2026-03-13] Added callback-chain continuation wiring for callback-style runtime modules. cart_button and checkout modules now declare equires_continuation, receive continuation_modules, and their core classes store/expose them. Runtime callback handlers for cart/checkout now run module continuations after callback action so subsequent steps execute only after interaction instead of every step running in one command pass.
[2026-03-13] Fixed callback continuation over-eager execution in inline/sending modules.\n- Added continuation-aware routing for inline_button and send_photo runtime modules by setting requires_continuation=True and passing continuation_modules from runtime_factory into core modules.\n- Extended core SendTelegramInlineButtonModule/SendTelegramPhotoModule to store continuation_modules and expose callback_data_keys for runtime callback matching.\n- Added callback fallback registry in bot_runtime_manager and runtime_update_router so unmatched callback_query data can execute continuation pipelines attached to callback-producing modules, preventing subsequent command modules from running immediately.\n- This addresses the regression where callback-capable modules executed subsequent modules in the same message pass.
[2026-03-13]
- Added per-message callback continuation routing to prevent callback replay on stale/duplicate callback_data.
- `src/etrax/standalone/runtime_update_router.py`:
  - Added per-message callback continuation map lookups keyed by `bot_id:chat_id:message_id:callback_data`.
  - Added registration of continuation routes from sent module results (using message_id) during pipeline execution.
  - For fallback continuations, execute only the next module step (not the whole remaining pipeline) so one callback advances one module.
- `src/etrax/standalone/bot_runtime_manager.py`:
  - Added runtime-held `callback_continuation_by_message` map and passed it into `_handle_update`.
- Effect:
  - Clicking a callback now advances one continuation step instead of rerunning the whole remaining chain, and per-message map helps avoid the “repeating the last message” behavior caused by overlapping `callback_data`.

